{
  "stem": "15962.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] It took quite a bit of doing to persuade the Germans to allow this activity.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Whereas the grown-ups had assigned jobs-- some would be sent out for road work.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Others would work paving the street in-- in the camp, or building additional barracks.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Or when he was-- was sent somewhere for farm work.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And every day, these work groups would bring back dead comrades that would not be able to sustain the heavy work.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We had to also stand outside twice a day, once in the morning, once in the evening, to be counted.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And one of the privileges this educator, Herr Hirsch, received for the children, that we would be counted in the barrack rather than standing outside in the cold or-- or rain.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] We-- my father was ill on and off.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And when he was not ill, as a doctor, he was assigned to [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] look-- to-- to screen people for lice.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Lice carried typhus and other diseases, and because there was so much dirt, it-- and no-- lack of water for washing.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We were doing everything possible to kill the lice that were swarming over us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And doctors were assigned to do that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] When he was-- early on, I remember that he did not look well, and suffered a great deal.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And at that time, he was only 53 years old.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He went into the gas chambers later on, and I'll tell you about it in sequence.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] In March, March 7, to be specific, of 1944, exactly six months after the first transport of 5,000 arrived there, they were taken away by truck to the next camp.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
